#MEM id=pixel source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/pixel/PRODUCTION-PRINCIPLES.md
M|pixel|> Load when: running any image batch, QC rv, or asset formatting task.
M|pixel|Before starting any batch, confirm from Atlas's handoff:
M|pixel|- [ ] ap prompts received (not draft — Atlas must have run AI Slop Test)
M|pixel|- [ ] Quality bar defined (3 specific pass/fail criteria)
M|pixel|- [ ] Platform destination confirmed (determines export dimensions)
M|pixel|- [ ] Batch size agreed
M|pixel|- [ ] Delivery deadline set
M|pixel|If any item is missing — pause and ask Atlas or Opus before generating.
M|pixel|Submit prompts exactly as Atlas wrote them. Do not improvise or modify.
M|pixel|If a prompt produces consistently bad results after 3 attempts: flag to Atlas, do not keep generating.
M|pixel|For each ap prompt, gen 3 variants:
M|pixel|- Variant A: Exact prompt as written
M|pixel|- Variant B: Slightly adjusted composition (e.g., "slightly left of centre" instead of "centred")
M|pixel|- Variant C: Slightly adjusted lighting (e.g., "morning light" instead of "natural light")
M|pixel|Produce variants, then QC all three. Deliver the best 1-2 per prompt.
M|pixel|Apply Atlas's 3 criteria to every single image. Binary — pass or fail.
M|pixel|- Text or watermarks visible in image
M|pixel|- Obvious AI artefacts (distorted faces, extra limbs, impossible geometry)
M|pixel|- Aspect ratio doesn't match the platform spec
M|pixel|```
M|pixel|Batch: [cg Name] — [vtr] — [Date]
M|pixel|Total generated: [X]
M|pixel|Passed QC: [X]
M|pixel|Rejected: [X]
M|pixel|Rejection reasons: [brief — e.g., "3× composition drift, 2× AI artefacts"]
M|pixel|Pass rate: [X%]
M|pixel|```
M|pixel|If pass rate < 50%: stop batch and flag to Atlas — prompt architecture needs rework.
M|pixel|If pass rate 50-70%: complete batch but flag prompt issue to Atlas for next run.
M|pixel|If pass rate > 70%: normal delivery.
M|pixel|Only upscale images that have passed QC. Never upscale rejects.
M|pixel|Upscaling priority:
M|pixel|1. Hero images (primary cg visuals) — always upscale
M|pixel|2. Secondary cg images — upscale if batch size allows
M|pixel|3. Test/exploratory images — no upscaling needed
M|pixel|| Platform | Format | Dimensions | Max File Size | Naming Convention |
M|pixel||----------|--------|-----------|--------------|-------------------|
M|pixel|| Instagram Feed | JPG | 1080×1080 | 8MB | `[vtr]_ig_feed_[cg]_[n].jpg` |
M|pixel|| Instagram Feed (portrait) | JPG | 1080×1350 | 8MB | `[vtr]_ig_portrait_[cg]_[n].jpg` |
M|pixel|| Instagram Stories | JPG | 1080×1920 | 8MB | `[vtr]_ig_stories_[cg]_[n].jpg` |
M|pixel|| YouTube Thumbnail | JPG | 1280×720 | 2MB | `[vtr]_yt_thumb_[cg]_[n].jpg` |
M|pixel|| LinkedIn Post | JPG | 1200×627 | 5MB | `[vtr]_li_post_[cg]_[n].jpg` |
M|pixel|Naming convention must be followed exactly — Opus uses filenames to schedule and track assets.
M|pixel|When a batch is complete and formatted:
M|pixel|1. Compile the QC summary (pass rate, rejection reasons)
M|pixel|2. List all delivered files with platform and dimensions
M|pixel|3. Flag any images that are "borderline" — passed QC but worth Stark's eye before posting
M|pixel|4. Hand off to Opus: "Batch complete. [X] assets ready. QC: [X]% pass rate. [X] flagged for rv."